 Implement and manage Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment (CI/CD) pipelines.
Use tools like Terraform, CloudFormation, or Ansible to automate infrastructure provisioning and management.
Use monitoring tools (e.g., CloudWatch, Azure Monitor, Stackdriver) to track system performance and health.
Optimization: Identify and implement optimizations to improve system performance and reduce costs.
Implement security best practices, including identity and access management (IAM), encryption, and network security.
Compliance: Ensure that cloud deployments comply with relevant regulations and standards.
Set up and maintain cloud infrastructure (e.g., servers, databases, storage) using platforms like AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud.
Resource Allocation: Ensure that resources are appropriately allocated and optimized for performance and cost efficiency